     I just want to say that this is a very excellent web site, Im only 18 years old, but I have alot of respect for the men who served in the Vietnam War.I feel that vietnam vets still today did not get the praise of the public they should recieve, I feel we owe them more then just a parade, we owe them our lives, freedom to them, because they made the total sacifice, there lives.They fought under very harsh treatment at home and Hell in vietnam to fight for Freedom on behalf of the American people and many people hated them for that.In my own opinion I feel our country was totally right to fight the  north vietnamese to spread our freedom to other countries.And on every veterans day I honor them by remembering those who gave there life for my freedom and aswell as others.I am a very patriotic person I love my country and respect the veterans of past to present wars,I support my countries military decissions fully.I proudly show the American Flage in front of my house,MY GOD BLESS EVERY VET FROM WW 1 through Desert storm,We should always remember those who fought and died for are freedom always..
